68) Construct a PHP script that catches a division by zero error using try-catch.
<?php
try {
$a = 10;
$b = 0;
if ($b == 0) {
throw new Exception("Division by zero is not allowed!");
}
$result = $a / $b;
echo "Result: $result";
} catch (Exception $e) {
echo "Error: " . $e->getMessage();
}
?>
Output
Error: Division by zero is not allowed!
